children.subject: The new system does not yet have the functionality to check for prerequisites, but 16A is a pre-req for 16B. You should not enroll in 16B if you have not taken 16A.
I'm guessing EECS of LSCS seats are set aside only if we've have taken EE16A beforehand, or does that not matter?

I'm sorry, I meant to write: 
If we are not yet declared EECS/CS, and have already taken EE16A, and have currently Phased 1 EE16B and are currently on the waitlist, is it safe to say I will NOT be purged from the waitlist, since I am waitlist for the group of non-(EECS/CS soph-seniors)? 
Can someone confirm?

Not necessarily. 16B is not as impacted as 16A. If you really want to take this class in fall I would suggest staying on the waitlist through Phase II. Then we will know how many of the reserved seats were not used and they will open. There are only 12 people on the waitlist right now, including you. I would think you have a very good chance of getting into this class.
Thank you very much for your help and quick response Lydia!

Would someone be able to confirm the following?:
If we are not yet declared EECS/CS, will we be purged from the EE16B waitlist (in June) if we Phase 1 the class?
From my understanding above, seats for the two groups above will remain empty while everyone else can continuously fill in the remaining seats.

history.content:
Seats will be set aside for the following students until August 15:

  1. EECS sophomores through seniors
  2. LSCS sophomores through seniors

 If you fall into the above categories, you can use Phase II units to enroll. As always, you should monitor the enrollment and adjust as needed.
 
After Aug 15, the unused seats will be released.
history.subject: Enrollment Procedure for EE16B, Fall '16
